## Tech Stack
- Golang 1.23.4
- SQLC for database querying
- Database migrations handled manually on `backend/internal/_shared/database/migrations`
- JWT authentication
- Docker and Docker Compose to handle development and testing databases
- Postgres 18

## Folder Organization
- Access entry points: `backend/cmd`
- API settings: `backend/cmd/api`
- Modules: `backend/internal`
- Shared content across different modules: `backend/internal/_shared`
- Shared custom errors: `backend/internal/_shared/custom-error`
- Database settings: `backend/internal/_shared/database`
- Utilities: `backend/internal/_shared/utils`
- Shared value objects: `backend/internal/_shared/value-objects`

## Module Folders Structure
- Located at `backend/internal`
- Have at least one of these 3 folders: `application`, `domain` and `infrastructure`
- They follow Clean Architecture and SOLID patterns
- `domain` folder has `entities` and `value-objects`
- Entities are identities with business rules
- Value Objects are attributes with validation or extra resources. They must be immutable and avoid obsession by primitive types
- `application` folder has `repositories` and `use-cases`
- Repositories from `application` are only interfaces for methods used to query database
- Use Cases are the business logic without any external concrete dependency
- `infrastructure` folder has `controllers`, `factories`, `mappers` and `repositories`
- Controllers are responsible to receive HTTP requests, parse payload, call Use Case and send response
- Factories from `infrastructure` build dependency injection for Use Case to make it works on Controllers layer
- Mappers take Use Case or Repository responses and convert it between different layers format data
- Repositories from `infrastructure` are implementation of a real database of repository interface on `application` folder

## Testing
- All Use Cases, Entities, Value Objects either from _shared or domain must be tested with unit tests and injecting stub dependencies created on `backend/test/unit` folder.
- All Controllers must be tested with integration tests carrying about clearing database between each running and preparing docker test database. You can implement extra resources in `backend/test/integration`.
- With unit tests cover success situations and returns with reproducible custom errors. An example of non-reproducible error are RepositoryError.
- With integration tests cover the success path and only the most one common error path.

## Standards
- Use structs like classes are used in OOP to create Use Cases, Controllers, Entities, Value Objects, etc
- Any doubt about Domain, Entities, Value Objects, Use Cases, Controllers, etc, you can search about Clean Architecture and SOLID principles on web
- Always check related or similar existing implementations before suggest or implement new one to avoid code duplicity or break code patterns